# World Cup Family Draft — environment
#
# Sharing is OPTIONAL. With no config the app persists to localStorage on a
# single device (great for trying it out). To let the whole family play together
# across devices, point it at a Supabase project:
#
#   1. Create a project at https://supabase.com
#   2. Run supabase/migrations/20260607000000_app_kv.sql in the SQL editor
#   3. Copy the values below from Project Settings → API
#   4. Restart `npm run dev`
#
# Then share the in-app invite link (it carries a ?league= code) so everyone
# lands in the same pool.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# --- Live results (football-data.org) ---
# Server-side ONLY — used by the /api/results serverless proxy, never exposed to
# the browser. Get a free token at https://www.football-data.org/client/register
# Set this in your Vercel project's Environment Variables (not committed).
#   FOOTBALL_DATA_COMPETITION defaults to "WC" (FIFA World Cup) if unset.
FOOTBALL_DATA_TOKEN=
FOOTBALL_DATA_COMPETITION=WC
